lia galaxies define a global relation down to Mv ~ -13. We also find,\nfor early-type dwarfs, no clear relation between luminosity and effective\nradius, indicating a nearly constant mean effective radius of ~ 1 kpc. This\nvalue is also found in several samples of dwarf galaxies in Virgo and Coma.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Mar 2008 17:16:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-05-19"}
